    <div>
        <h1>How to Create Custom Campaign Template</h1>

        <h2>Creating New Templates</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Log In: Access your account and navigate to the dashboard.</li>
            <li>Access Templates: Locate the "Templates" section in the main menu.</li>
            <img src="/img/Template1.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>New Template: Click on "Add Template" option to start creating a new template.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template2.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        <img src="/img/Template3.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Template Details: Enter the template name, and select the template type (e.g., Email, SMS, WhatsApp, etc.).</li>
        <img src="/img/Template4.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Content Creation: Use the provided dragand drop feature to create the your template. Include placeholders for dynamic data if needed and also you can generate this data through AI (Hading,Images, etc.) everything can be generated through AI by clicking on "See Magic button".</li>
        <img src="/img/Template5.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        <img src="/img/Template6.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Save Template: Once satisfied with the content, Click on save button and you will get the success popup.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template7.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        <img src="/img/Template8.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        </ol>

        <h2>Downloading Templates</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Navigate to Templates: Access the "All Templates" section from the main menu under the "Template" section.</li>
        
            <li>View Templates: Browse through the list of available templates.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template9.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">

        <li>Download:Click on the download option and Download all the templates.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template10.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Save File: Save the downloaded template file to your desired location on your computer.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Viewing Templates</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Access Templates: Log in to your account and go to the "Templates" section.</li>
            <li>Browse Templates: FInd the "Eye icon" through the list of templates to find the one you want to view.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template11.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>View Details: Click on the "Eye Icon" associated to the template name or details option to view the template content.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template12.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Preview: Review the template content, layout, and any dynamic elements.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Editing Templates</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Access Templates: Log in and navigate to the "Templates" section.</li>
            <li>Find Template: Locate the template you wish to edit from the list.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template13.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Edit Option: Click on the edit option next to the template name.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template5.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Modify Content: Use the editor to make changes to the template content, such as updating text, images, links, etc.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template6.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
            <li>Save Changes: After editing, save the changes to update the template.</li>
        <img src="/img/Template7.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        <img src="/img/Template8.png" alt="Screenshot of accessing campaign creation page">
        </ol>
    </div>

